which used different names for the sexual and asexual phases of pleomorphic species. The next, and more difficult, step will be to develop community standards for sequence-based classification.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Hibbett","given":"David S.","literal":""},{"family":"Hibbett","given":"David S.","literal":""},{"family":"Taylor","given":"John W.","literal":""},{"family":"Taylor","given":"John W.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"hibbett_fungal_2013","year":"2013","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Fungal systematics: is a new age of enlightenment at hand?"],"author-links":["[[Author/David S. Hibbett]]","[[Author/David S. Hibbett]]","[[Author/John W. Taylor]]","[[Author/John W. Taylor]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/hibbett_fungal_2013/hibbett_fungal_2013.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"zf469h","at":1774951889466}},"smart_blocks:Research/@hibbett_fungal_2013.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.03014806,0.00145819,0.04287861,0.01419257,0.00953598,0.00187213,-0.05066966,0.0274284,-0.03658609,0.03384878,0.01185517,-0.01963419,-0.00523247,-0.00374894,-0.02269947,0.01575348,0.01816738,0.02910283,-0.04372182,0.03102214,0.1345937,-0.01186037,-0.02027306,0.02114509,0.04553326,0.06466903,0.00808632,-0.07860849,-0.04759774,-0.24023505,-0.05042469,0.04419676,0.00136691,-0.02138242,0.00614324,-0.03663692,-0.05948319,-0.023782,-0.0239603,0.03868477,0.01554456,0.04204023,0.01122813,0.0281838,-0.05911844,-0.07396903,-0.0289169,0.01103266,-0.0785321,-0.05914095,-0.07825228,-0.04507614,0.00067498,0.01250479,-0.02278296,0.01567653,0.0329022,0.0186868,0.0359793,0.00521602,0.10768088,0.05593434,-0.16305716,0.12055249,0.01853903,0.00109266,-0.09691387,-0.02420462,0.05791673,0.00199675,0.03627074,0.00781405,0.04704885,0.04458145,0.07799578,-0.02450876,-0.00578502,-0.07706112,-0.02135557,-0.036819,0.00815899,0.05774183,-0.02